text:
29 Seconds of Farcaster ... What did you miss this weekend?

* $ZORA is on a crazy run tied to TBA coining of posts, which has led to lots of discussion, some valuable, some less so.... and you guessed it, mixed reviews

* @tldr highlighted a breakthrough weekend for $BRACKY with the first in chat trading and a new all-time high market cap of $5m (also first F1 market)

* @jake noted that the first crowd funded $QR auction was organized & won by @zeni.eth & rocketed their mini app up the leaderboard & doubled the marketcap of $STREME

* @chronist neonified the timeline to support @betrmint 's crowdfund for NEONCHAIN Summer... what started as a few hours turned into a few days of redoing pfps in his distinct style and filling the feed with bangers

* @mjc716 teased $PROCOIN mini app 'FEEDS' under soft launch and @jdotfinn was hyping the curation model & noted the mini app was #5 pre-launch

* This Week In Mini Apps @limone.eth joined @linda here: https://farcaster.xyz/linda/0x77c581bd & also limone dropped an article 'The New Economic Stack For Creators' https://farcaster.xyz/limone.eth/0xc43baf96

* @adrienne & @nounishprof are on today at 11:30 AM EST/ 8:30 PST to cover all things Farcaster to start your week

text:
HOLD THE CUBE 

Here‚Äòs a prompt for your PFP to hold the @base.base.eth Cube üëáüèΩ

Use the provided user photo as the main subject. Make it look like the person in the image is holding a cube in their hands.

The cube must be a perfect, smooth, solid blue cube with rounded corners, exactly like this: a square shape with evenly curved edges, pure intense #0000FF royal blue, evenly filled, no texture, no reflections, no gradients.

The cube must match this reference image exactly ‚Äî same shape, color, size ratio and corner radius. It should be placed realistically in the person‚Äôs hands, as if they are holding it carefully.

Make sure the lighting and shadows make the cube feel integrated into the original photo.

@jesse.base.eth @buildonbase

text:
Introducing: A Shitcaster's Guide to Farcaster

Context is hard to find especially if you're new. 

So, we made a guide for all the Farcaster lore, projects, memes, and so much more.

This is a growing list, I suggest you bookmark this article.

https://paragraph.com/@readme/guide

html.ogDescription: You're here because someone said "frames" and you smiled and nodded like you knew what that meant. It's okay. We all did. Context is hard to find, especially if you're new. Everyone's speaking meme, half the words are inside-jokes, and the other half are just nonsense. So we made this. A guide that actually explains what things mean. It'll keep growing as the lore does.
